<subSubSection id="609461302C5B2A9D8665CF7FFF9E7F54" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="3B0B0D3F568CA23470BF573A29558619" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BCB17A6FC19BFB0ACDC0DB524D7611A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName id="018503D9B736E994D4D67A160ABD8033" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce torchaceus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torchaceus">
<emphasis id="E3CF2E84F8B3B1B40B950B29BBD789CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce torchaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Feng and Woo, 1999 was established based on the samples form Mt. Wuyi and Mt. Jianfengling, which was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="D379F5720DB156EF7CF195E79D792D5F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.337.5770" author="Wang, ZQ" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" pagination="1 - 18" refId="B55" refString="Wang, ZQ, Che, YL, 2013. Three new species of cockroach genus Symploce Hebard, 1916 (Blattodea, Ectobiidae, Blattellinae) with redescriptions of two known species based on types from Mainland China. ZooKeys 337: 1 - 18, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.337.5770" title="Three new species of cockroach genus Symploce Hebard, 1916 (Blattodea, Ectobiidae, Blattellinae) with redescriptions of two known species based on types from Mainland China." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.337.5770" volume="337" year="2013">Wang and Che (2013)</bibRefCitation>
where the detailed information on genitalia was provided for the first time. Herein, we transfer this species to genus 
<taxonomicName id="EDD791F3E87D4334FFEB2C0A10D8DAEF" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6B22F4B98C61299246018B70E30C4F5F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on basis of characteristics as follows: body medium-sized; posterior margin of subgenital plate slightly thickened and setaceous. And in our ML and BI inferences 
<taxonomicName id="2CCAA9A92751BF9CD46385C9823A700A" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce torchaceus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torchaceus">
<emphasis id="C4EDADE08C16AFF7BC30BC3B66442706" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce torchaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Feng and Woo, 1999 was grouped together with other 
<taxonomicName id="9D125D65774288906B70170A028467E1" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C14792B3FA7DE5BC8395C5473881CEA9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
members forming a monophyletic group (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B83C14D3BE30509EC4FBF34808163556" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on three mitochondrial genes 12 S rRNA, 16 S rRNA, COII and two nuclear genes 28 S rRNA, histone H 3. The topologies yielded by Bayesian inference (BI) are almost identical with ML tree (see supplementary material Fig. S 1). Branch labels provide bootstrap support (bs) of nodes in ML and posterior probability (pp) (%) of nodes in BI; (*) indicates the branch label of the corresponding analysis is 100 or 1.0, respectively; (-) means the node is absent for the given analysis." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690401" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">1</figureCitation>
, supplementary material Fig. S1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
